OL,3,CDeputies approve plans for 500 housing
OL,4,Cunits at Black Rock
OL,6,FGuernsey's politicians have voted to
OL,7,Fgo ahead with plans to store inert
OL,8,Fwaste at Black Rock - which could
OL,9,Fpotentially open up the area for
OL,10,Faround 500 units of housing.
OL,12,FThe proposals, which were voted
OL,13,Fthrough by 34 votes to two , will
OL,14,Fallow for the homes to be built on top
OL,15,Fof the inert waste - which will start
OL,16,Fbeing stockpiled in three years time.
OL,18,FDeputies also approved the use of Les
OL,19,FVardes Quarry for water storage, by 19
OL,20,Fvotes to 14, after a vote passed to
OL,21,Fseparate the two proposals.
